    "id": 3022,
    "question": "Over the course of a week, Du Chin bakes and sells meat pies every day. On Monday, he sells 200 meat pies, but his sales fluctuate daily, increasing by 10% on Tuesday, decreasing by 5% on Wednesday, staying the same on Thursday, increasing by 15% on Friday, decreasing by 8% on Saturday, and finally increasing by 5% on Sunday. Du Chin sells these pies for $20 each. \n\nAdditionally, his daily ingredient costs fluctuate. On Monday, he spends 3/5 of his sales on ingredients. On Tuesday, this increases by 10%, and then decreases by 10% on Wednesday. The cost remains the same on Thursday, increases by 5% on Friday, decreases by 5% on Saturday, and finally stays the same on Sunday.\n\nFind out how much money Du Chin remains with after setting aside the money for buying ingredients each day over the week.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the number of pies sold each day and the corresponding sales and ingredient costs.\n\n**Monday:**\n- Pies sold: 200\n- Sales: 200 pies * $20/pie = $4000\n- Ingredient cost: 3/5 of $4000 = $2400\n- Remaining: $4000 - $2400 = $1600\n\n**Tuesday:**\n- Pies sold: 200 pies + 10% of 200 pies = 200 pies + 20 pies = 220 pies\n- Sales: 220 pies * $20/pie = $4400\n- Ingredient cost: $2400 + 10% of $2400 = $2400 + $240 = $2640\n- Remaining: $4400 - $2640 = $1760\n\n**Wednesday:**\n- Pies sold: 220 pies - 5% of 220 pies = 220 pies - 11 pies = 209 pies\n- Sales: 209 pies * $20/pie = $4180\n- Ingredient cost: $2640 - 10% of $2640 = $2640 - $264 = $2376\n- Remaining: $4180 - $2376 = $1804\n\n**Thursday:**\n- Pies sold: 209 pies (same as Wednesday)\n- Sales: 209 pies * $20/pie = $4180\n- Ingredient cost: $2376 (same as Wednesday)\n- Remaining: $4180 - $2376 = $1804\n\n**Friday:**\n- Pies sold: 209 pies + 15% of 209 pies = 209 pies + 31.35 pies ≈ 240 pies (rounded down)\n- Sales: 240 pies * $20/pie = $4800\n- Ingredient cost: $2376 + 5% of $2376 = $2376 + $118.80 = $2494.80\n- Remaining: $4800 - $2494.80 = $2305.20\n\n**Saturday:**\n- Pies sold: 240 pies - 8% of 240 pies = 240 pies - 19.2 pies ≈ 221 pies (rounded down)\n- Sales: 221 pies * $20/pie = $4420\n- Ingredient cost: $2494.80 - 5% of $2494.80 = $2494.80 - $124.74 = $2370.06\n- Remaining: $4420 - $2370.06 = $2049.94\n\n**Sunday:**\n- Pies sold: 221 pies + 5% of 221 pies = 221 pies + 11.05 pies ≈ 232 pies (rounded down)\n- Sales: 232 pies * $20/pie = $4640\n- Ingredient cost: $2370.06 (same as Saturday)\n- Remaining: $4640 - $2370.06 = $2269.94\n\nNow, let's add up the remaining money for each day to find out the total amount Du Chin has after setting aside the money for ingredients:\n\nTotal remaining = $1600 + $1760 + $1804 + $1804 + $2305.20 + $2049.94 + $2269.94\nTotal remaining = $13589.08\n\nDu Chin remains with $13589.08 after setting aside the money for buying ingredients each day over the week.",
