    "id": 3023,
    "question": "The following data is available for three major global payment processing companies over the past five years:\n\n- Company X: \n    - Year 1 Revenue: $150 billion, Expenses: $100 billion\n    - Year 5 Revenue: $130 billion, Expenses: $90 billion\n\n- Company Y: \n    - Year 1 Revenue: $200 billion, Expenses: $160 billion\n    - Year 5 Revenue: $170 billion, Expenses: $140 billion\n\n- Company Z: \n    - Year 1 Revenue: $250 billion, Expenses: $200 billion\n    - Year 5 Revenue: $210 billion, Expenses: $170 billion\n\nCalculate the percentage change in revenue, expenses, and net profit margin (Net Profit Margin = (Revenue - Expenses) / Revenue * 100%) from Year 1 to Year 5 for each company. Also, determine the average percentage change in revenue, expenses, and net profit margin across all three companies over this period.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "First, let's calculate the percentage change in revenue, expenses, and net profit margin for each company from Year 1 to Year 5.\n\n**Company X:**\n\n- Revenue Change: \\((130 - 150) / 150 * 100\\% = (-20 / 150) * 100\\% = -13.33\\%\\)\n- Expenses Change: \\((90 - 100) / 100 * 100\\% = (-10 / 100) * 100\\% = -10\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Year 1: \\((150 - 100) / 150 * 100\\% = 50 / 150 * 100\\% = 33.33\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Year 5: \\((130 - 90) / 130 * 100\\% = 40 / 130 * 100\\% = 30.77\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Change: \\(30.77\\% - 33.33\\% = -2.56\\%\\)\n\n**Company Y:**\n\n- Revenue Change: \\((170 - 200) / 200 * 100\\% = (-30 / 200) * 100\\% = -15\\%\\)\n- Expenses Change: \\((140 - 160) / 160 * 100\\% = (-20 / 160) * 100\\% = -12.5\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Year 1: \\((200 - 160) / 200 * 100\\% = 40 / 200 * 100\\% = 20\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Year 5: \\((170 - 140) / 170 * 100\\% = 30 / 170 * 100\\% = 17.65\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Change: \\(17.65\\% - 20\\% = -2.35\\%\\)\n\n**Company Z:**\n\n- Revenue Change: \\((210 - 250) / 250 * 100\\% = (-40 / 250) * 100\\% = -16\\%\\)\n- Expenses Change: \\((170 - 200) / 200 * 100\\% = (-30 / 200) * 100\\% = -15\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Year 1: \\((250 - 200) / 250 * 100\\% = 50 / 250 * 100\\% = 20\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Year 5: \\((210 - 170) / 210 * 100\\% = 40 / 210 * 100\\% = 19.05\\%\\)\n- Net Profit Margin Change: \\(19.05\\% - 20\\% = -0.95\\%\\)\n\nNow, let's calculate the average percentage change across all three companies:\n\n**Average Revenue Change:**\n\\((-13.33\\% - 15\\% - 16\\%) / 3 = (-44.33\\%) / 3 = -14.78\\%\\)\n\n**Average Expenses Change:**\n\\((-10\\% - 12.5\\% - 15\\%) / 3 = (-37.5\\%) / 3 = -12.5\\%\\)\n\n**Average Net Profit Margin Change:**\n\\((-2.56\\% - 2.35\\% - 0.95\\%) / 3 = (-5.86\\%) / 3 = -1.95\\%\\)\n\nSo, the average percentage change in revenue across all three companies is -14.78%, in expenses is -12.5%, and in net profit margin is -1.95%.",
