    "id": 3024,
    "question": "Over the course of a week, Kelly started taking inventory of different baking ingredients at her pastry shop each day. The table below shows the quantity of these ingredients on the first and the last days of the week:\n\n- Baking powder (unit: lbs):      Day 1 - 12 lbs,       Day 7 - 6 lbs\n- Flour (unit: kg):                Day 1 - 6 kg,         Day 7 - 3.5 kg\n- Sugar (unit: lbs):               Day 1 - 20 lbs,       Day 7 - 15 lbs\n- Chocolate chips (unit: g):       Day 1 - 5000 g,      Day 7 - 1500 g\n\nTo restock her ingredients, she needs to know the change in each ingredient's quantity and their costs. The following are the costs of ingredients:\n\n- Baking powder:  $3.00 per pound\n- Flour:           $1.50 per pound \n- Sugar:           $0.50 per pound\n- Chocolate chips: $0.015 per gram\n\nFirst, determine the change in each ingredient's quantity over the week by converting the amounts of flour and chocolate chips to pounds (Note: 1 kg = 2.20462 lbs and 1 g = 0.00220462 lbs). Next, find out the cost Kelly needs to spend on replenishing each ingredient, based on their change in quantity and individual prices. Finally, calculate the total cost to replenish all the ingredients.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "First, let's calculate the change in quantity for each ingredient:\n\n1. Baking powder:\n   Change = Day 1 - Day 7\n   Change = 12 lbs - 6 lbs\n   Change = 6 lbs\n\n2. Flour:\n   Day 1 in lbs = 6 kg * 2.20462 lbs/kg\n   Day 1 in lbs = 13.22772 lbs\n   Day 7 in lbs = 3.5 kg * 2.20462 lbs/kg\n   Day 7 in lbs = 7.71617 lbs\n   Change = Day 1 in lbs - Day 7 in lbs\n   Change = 13.22772 lbs - 7.71617 lbs\n   Change = 5.51155 lbs\n\n3. Sugar:\n   Change = Day 1 - Day 7\n   Change = 20 lbs - 15 lbs\n   Change = 5 lbs\n\n4. Chocolate chips:\n   Day 1 in lbs = 5000 g * 0.00220462 lbs/g\n   Day 1 in lbs = 11.0231 lbs\n   Day 7 in lbs = 1500 g * 0.00220462 lbs/g\n   Day 7 in lbs = 3.30693 lbs\n   Change = Day 1 in lbs - Day 7 in lbs\n   Change = 11.0231 lbs - 3.30693 lbs\n   Change = 7.71617 lbs\n\nNow, let's calculate the cost to replenish each ingredient:\n\n1. Baking powder:\n   Cost = Change in quantity * Price per pound\n   Cost = 6 lbs * $3.00/lb\n   Cost = $18.00\n\n2. Flour:\n   Cost = Change in quantity * Price per pound\n   Cost = 5.51155 lbs * $1.50/lb\n   Cost = $8.267325 (rounded to $8.27)\n\n3. Sugar:\n   Cost = Change in quantity * Price per pound\n   Cost = 5 lbs * $0.50/lb\n   Cost = $2.50\n\n4. Chocolate chips:\n   Cost = Change in quantity * Price per gram\n   Cost = 7.71617 lbs * $0.015/g\n   Since the price is given per gram, we need to convert the change in pounds back to grams:\n   Change in grams = 7.71617 lbs * (1 lb / 0.00220462 g)\n   Change in grams = 3500 g (since we started with 5000 g and ended with 1500 g)\n   Cost = 3500 g * $0.015/g\n   Cost = $52.50\n\nFinally, let's calculate the total cost to replenish all ingredients:\n\nTotal cost = Cost of Baking powder + Cost of Flour + Cost of Sugar + Cost of Chocolate chips\nTotal cost = $18.00 + $8.27 + $2.50 + $52.50\nTotal cost = $81.27\n\nKelly needs to spend $81.27 to replenish all the ingredients.",
