    "question": "In a city, the population in the year 2000 was 1,000,000. The population's growth rate varied over the next decade as follows:\n- In 2001, there was an increase of 12%;\n- In 2002, there was a decrease of 8%;\n- In 2003, there was an increase of 15%;\n- In 2004, there was an increase of 5%;\n- In 2005, there was a decrease of 10%;\n- In 2006, there was an increase of 18%;\n- In 2007, there was a decrease of 15%;\n- In 2008, there was an increase of 10%;\n- In 2009, there was a decrease of 5%;\n- In 2010, there was an increase of 20%.\n\nFind the population of the city at the end of the year 2010.\n\n### Answer:",
