    "explanation": "To find the population at the end of the year 2010, we need to apply each year's growth rate to the population of the previous year. Let's calculate it step by step:\n\nInitial population in 2000: 1,000,000\n\n2001: Increase of 12%\nPopulation = 1,000,000 + (12/100 * 1,000,000) = 1,000,000 + 120,000 = 1,120,000\n\n2002: Decrease of 8%\nPopulation = 1,120,000 - (8/100 * 1,120,000) = 1,120,000 - 89,600 = 1,030,400\n\n2003: Increase of 15%\nPopulation = 1,030,400 + (15/100 * 1,030,400) = 1,030,400 + 154,560 = 1,184,960\n\n2004: Increase of 5%\nPopulation = 1,184,960 + (5/100 * 1,184,960) = 1,184,960 + 59,248 = 1,244,208\n\n2005: Decrease of 10%\nPopulation = 1,244,208 - (10/100 * 1,244,208) = 1,244,208 - 124,420.8 = 1,119,787.2\n\n2006: Increase of 18%\nPopulation = 1,119,787.2 + (18/100 * 1,119,787.2) = 1,119,787.2 + 201,561.696 = 1,321,348.896\n\n2007: Decrease of 15%\nPopulation = 1,321,348.896 - (15/100 * 1,321,348.896) = 1,321,348.896 - 198,202.3344 = 1,123,146.5616\n\n2008: Increase of 10%\nPopulation = 1,123,146.5616 + (10/100 * 1,123,146.5616) = 1,123,146.5616 + 112,314.65616 = 1,235,461.21776\n\n2009: Decrease of 5%\nPopulation = 1,235,461.21776 - (5/100 * 1,235,461.21776) = 1,235,461.21776 - 61,773.060888 = 1,173,688.15687\n\n2010: Increase of 20%\nPopulation = 1,173,688.15687 + (20/100 * 1,173,688.15687) = 1,173,688.15687 + 234,737.631374 = 1,408,425.78824\n\nTherefore, the population at the end of the year 2010 is approximately 1,408,426 (rounded to the nearest whole number).",
