    "question": "On Friday, Remy paid Sally's Woodworking LLC a total of $20,700 for a bulk purchase of 150 pieces of furniture, consisting of chairs, tables, and cabinets. For every 3 chairs, Remy bought 5 tables and 2 cabinets. The base prices for chairs, tables, and cabinets are $120, $220, and $340 respectively. The company offered tiered discounts based on the quantity of each item purchased:\n\n- Chairs: 10% discount if purchasing 15 or more, and an additional 5% discount if purchasing 30 or more.\n- Tables: 5% discount if purchasing 25 or more, and an additional 3% discount if purchasing 40 or more.\n- Cabinets: 2% discount if purchasing 10 or more, and an additional 5% discount if purchasing 20 or more.\n\nAdditionally, there was a 7% sales tax applied to the total payment after discounts, and a $250 delivery charge along with a $350 assembly charge. Later that evening, the company's accountant discovered that a new intern in the sales department had overcharged Remy by not applying the tiered discounts and additional fees correctly. How much money will Sally's Woodworking LLC reimburse Remy?\n\n### Answer:",
