    "id": 3072,
    "question": "In a city, the population in 1995 was 250,000 people. The population underwent the following changes each subsequent year: In 1996, it increased by 15%; in 1997, it decreased by 10%; in 1998, it increased by 25%; in 1999, it decreased by 30%; in the year 2000, it increased again by 40%; in 2001, it decreased by 35%; in 2002, it increased by 50%; in 2003, it decreased by 45% and in 2004, the population finally increased by 20%. Find the population of the city at the end of the year 2004.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "To find the population at the end of the year 2004, we need to apply each year's percentage change to the population of the previous year.\n\nLet's calculate it step by step:\n\n1. 1995: The population is 250,000.\n\n2. 1996: The population increased by 15%.\n   New population = 250,000 + (15/100 * 250,000)\n                  = 250,000 + 37,500\n                  = 287,500\n\n3. 1997: The population decreased by 10%.\n   New population = 287,500 - (10/100 * 287,500)\n                  = 287,500 - 28,750\n                  = 258,750\n\n4. 1998: The population increased by 25%.\n   New population = 258,750 + (25/100 * 258,750)\n                  = 258,750 + 64,687.5\n                  = 323,437.5\n\n5. 1999: The population decreased by 30%.\n   New population = 323,437.5 - (30/100 * 323,437.5)\n                  = 323,437.5 - 97,031.25\n                  = 226,406.25\n\n6. 2000: The population increased by 40%.\n   New population = 226,406.25 + (40/100 * 226,406.25)\n                  = 226,406.25 + 90,562.5\n                  = 316,968.75\n\n7. 2001: The population decreased by 35%.\n   New population = 316,968.75 - (35/100 * 316,968.75)\n                  = 316,968.75 - 110,939.0625\n                  = 206,029.6875\n\n8. 2002: The population increased by 50%.\n   New population = 206,029.6875 + (50/100 * 206,029.6875)\n                  = 206,029.6875 + 103,014.84375\n                  = 309,044.53125\n\n9. 2003: The population decreased by 45%.\n   New population = 309,044.53125 - (45/100 * 309,044.53125)\n                  = 309,044.53125 - 139,070.0390625\n                  = 169,974.4921875\n\n10. 2004: The population increased by 20%.\n    New population = 169,974.4921875 + (20/100 * 169,974.4921875)\n                   = 169,974.4921875 + 33,994.8984375\n                   = 203,969.390625\n\nTherefore, the population of the city at the end of the year 2004 was approximately 203,969 people.",
