    "id": 3073,
    "question": "Robbie is tracking his nutrition intake per week. He eats 3 cups of rice, 8 ounces of chicken, and 2 cups of vegetables in the morning; 2 cups of rice, a cup of beans, and 6 ounces of beef in the afternoon; and 5 cups of rice, half a cup of cheese, and 10 almonds in the evening.\n\nIf a cup of rice has 10 grams of fat, 45 grams of carbohydrates, and 5 grams of protein; 1 ounce of chicken has 2 grams of fat, 0 grams of carbohydrates, and 7 grams of protein; 1 cup of vegetables has 0.3 grams of fat, 5 grams of carbohydrates, and 2 grams of protein; 1 cup of beans has 1 gram of fat, 40 grams of carbohydrates, and 15 grams of protein; 1 ounce of beef has 6 grams of fat, 0 grams of carbohydrates, and 7 grams of protein; half a cup of cheese has 18 grams of fat, 2 grams of carbohydrates, and 14 grams of protein; and 10 almonds have 6 grams of fat, 2 grams of carbohydrates, and 3 grams of protein. \n\nCalculate Robbie's total intake of fat, carbohydrates, and protein per day, and then find his weekly intake of each nutrient.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate Robbie's daily intake first:\n\nMorning:\n- Rice: 3 cups * (10g fat, 45g carbs, 5g protein) = 30g fat, 135g carbs, 15g protein\n- Chicken: 8 ounces * (2g fat, 0g carbs, 7g protein) = 16g fat, 0g carbs, 56g protein\n- Vegetables: 2 cups * (0.3g fat, 5g carbs, 2g protein) = 0.6g fat, 10g carbs, 4g protein\n\nAfternoon:\n- Rice: 2 cups * (10g fat, 45g carbs, 5g protein) = 20g fat, 90g carbs, 10g protein\n- Beans: 1 cup * (1g fat, 40g carbs, 15g protein) = 1g fat, 40g carbs, 15g protein\n- Beef: 6 ounces * (6g fat, 0g carbs, 7g protein) = 36g fat, 0g carbs, 42g protein\n\nEvening:\n- Rice: 5 cups * (10g fat, 45g carbs, 5g protein) = 50g fat, 225g carbs, 25g protein\n- Cheese: 0.5 cups * (18g fat, 2g carbs, 14g protein) = 9g fat, 1g carbs, 7g protein\n- Almonds: 10 almonds * (6g fat, 2g carbs, 3g protein) = 6g fat, 2g carbs, 3g protein\n\nNow, let's add up the totals for each nutrient for the day:\n\nTotal fat: 30g + 16g + 0.6g + 20g + 1g + 36g + 50g + 9g + 6g = 168.6g\nTotal carbohydrates: 135g + 0g + 10g + 90g + 40g + 0g + 225g + 1g + 2g = 503g\nTotal protein: 15g + 56g + 4g + 10g + 15g + 42g + 25g + 7g + 3g = 177g\n\nNow, let's calculate Robbie's weekly intake:\n\nWeekly fat: 168.6g/day * 7 days = 1180.2g\nWeekly carbohydrates: 503g/day * 7 days = 3521g\nWeekly protein: 177g/day * 7 days = 1239g\n\nSo, Robbie's weekly intake of each nutrient is:\n- Fat: 1180.2 grams\n- Carbohydrates: 3521 grams\n- Protein: 1239 grams",
