    "id": 3077,
    "question": "A bathing suit manufacturer produces bathing suits in different styles and for different genders. They produce 2,500 one-piece bathing suits, 3,700 two-piece bathing suits for women, 1,800 swimming trunks, and 2,600 swimming shorts for men each month. At the beginning of June, they had an initial stock of 7,000 one-piece bathing suits, 10,000 two-piece bathing suits for women, 4,000 swimming trunks, and 6,000 swimming shorts for men.\n\nDuring the month of June, they managed to sell 40% of one-piece bathing suits, 50% of two-piece bathing suits for women, 65% of swimming trunks, and 70% of swimming shorts that were produced that month. In addition, they sold 15% of their initial stock of each category.\n\nConsidering the production, initial stock, and sales in June, how many bathing suits are available in each category at the end of the month?\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the number of bathing suits available in each category at the end of June step by step.\n\n**One-Piece Bathing Suits:**\n- Initial stock: 7,000\n- Produced in June: 2,500\n- Total available before sales: 7,000 + 2,500 = 9,500\n- Sold from June production (40% of 2,500): 0.40 * 2,500 = 1,000\n- Sold from initial stock (15% of 7,000): 0.15 * 7,000 = 1,050\n- Total sold: 1,000 + 1,050 = 2,050\n- Available at the end of June: 9,500 - 2,050 = 7,450\n\n**Two-Piece Bathing Suits for Women:**\n- Initial stock: 10,000\n- Produced in June: 3,700\n- Total available before sales: 10,000 + 3,700 = 13,700\n- Sold from June production (50% of 3,700): 0.50 * 3,700 = 1,850\n- Sold from initial stock (15% of 10,000): 0.15 * 10,000 = 1,500\n- Total sold: 1,850 + 1,500 = 3,350\n- Available at the end of June: 13,700 - 3,350 = 10,350\n\n**Swimming Trunks:**\n- Initial stock: 4,000\n- Produced in June: 1,800\n- Total available before sales: 4,000 + 1,800 = 5,800\n- Sold from June production (65% of 1,800): 0.65 * 1,800 = 1,170\n- Sold from initial stock (15% of 4,000): 0.15 * 4,000 = 600\n- Total sold: 1,170 + 600 = 1,770\n- Available at the end of June: 5,800 - 1,770 = 4,030\n\n**Swimming Shorts for Men:**\n- Initial stock: 6,000\n- Produced in June: 2,600\n- Total available before sales: 6,000 + 2,600 = 8,600\n- Sold from June production (70% of 2,600): 0.70 * 2,600 = 1,820\n- Sold from initial stock (15% of 6,000): 0.15 * 6,000 = 900\n- Total sold: 1,820 + 900 = 2,720\n- Available at the end of June: 8,600 - 2,720 = 5,880\n\nSo, at the end of June, the number of bathing suits available in each category is:\n- One-Piece Bathing Suits: 7,450\n- Two-Piece Bathing Suits for Women: 10,350\n- Swimming Trunks: 4,030\n- Swimming Shorts for Men: 5,880",
