    "id": 3083,
    "question": "Apple sold 100 iPhones at their New York store today for an average cost of $1000 each. They also sold 20 iPads with an average cost of $900 each, 80 Apple TVs at an average cost of $200 each, and 50 MacBooks at an average cost of $1500 each. In addition, each product category had an exclusive offer: iPhones had a 10% sales tax, iPads had a 5% discount, Apple TVs had an 8% sales tax, and MacBooks had a 15% discount. \n\nThe exchange rates for today are 1 USD = 0.85 EUR and 1 USD = 110 JPY. What was the average cost, including discounts and taxes, of each product category in both EUR and JPY? Calculate the total revenue in EUR and JPY for all products sold today.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "First, let's calculate the average cost including discounts and taxes for each product category in USD:\n\n1. iPhones:\n   - Average cost: $1000\n   - Sales tax: 10%\n   - Final average cost with tax: $1000 + ($1000 * 0.10) = $1000 + $100 = $1100\n\n2. iPads:\n   - Average cost: $900\n   - Discount: 5%\n   - Final average cost with discount: $900 - ($900 * 0.05) = $900 - $45 = $855\n\n3. Apple TVs:\n   - Average cost: $200\n   - Sales tax: 8%\n   - Final average cost with tax: $200 + ($200 * 0.08) = $200 + $16 = $216\n\n4. MacBooks:\n   - Average cost: $1500\n   - Discount: 15%\n   - Final average cost with discount: $1500 - ($1500 * 0.15) = $1500 - $225 = $1275\n\nNow, let's convert these costs to EUR and JPY using the given exchange rates:\n\n1 USD = 0.85 EUR\n1 USD = 110 JPY\n\nAverage cost in EUR:\n- iPhones: $1100 * 0.85 = €935\n- iPads: $855 * 0.85 = €726.75\n- Apple TVs: $216 * 0.85 = €183.60\n- MacBooks: $1275 * 0.85 = €1083.75\n\nAverage cost in JPY:\n- iPhones: $1100 * 110 = ¥121,000\n- iPads: $855 * 110 = ¥94,050\n- Apple TVs: $216 * 110 = ¥23,760\n- MacBooks: $1275 * 110 = ¥140,250\n\nNow, let's calculate the total revenue for all products sold today in USD and then convert to EUR and JPY:\n\nTotal revenue in USD:\n- iPhones: $1100 * 100 = $110,000\n- iPads: $855 * 20 = $17,100\n- Apple TVs: $216 * 80 = $17,280\n- MacBooks: $1275 * 50 = $63,750\n- Total revenue in USD: $110,000 + $17,100 + $17,280 + $63,750 = $208,130\n\nTotal revenue in EUR:\n- $208,130 * 0.85 = €176,910.50\n\nTotal revenue in JPY:\n- $208,130 * 110 = ¥22,894,300\n\nSo, the average cost of each product category in EUR and JPY is as follows:\n- iPhones: €935 and ¥121,000\n- iPads: €726.75 and ¥94,050\n- Apple TVs: €183.60 and ¥23,760\n- MacBooks: €1083.75 and ¥140,250\n\nAnd the total revenue for all products sold today in EUR and JPY is:\n- €176,910.50 and ¥22,894,300",
