    "id": 3084,
    "question": "Consider a group of five individuals, m, n, o, p, and q. The average monthly income of m and n is Rs. 5050, the average monthly income of n and o is Rs. 6250, the average monthly income of o and p is Rs. 6800, and the average monthly income of p and q is Rs. 7500. Additionally, the average monthly income of m, o, and q is Rs. 6000. Find the monthly income of each individual m, n, o, p, and q.\n\n### Answer:",
    "options": [
      "Option A",
      "Option B",
      "Option C",
      "Option D"
    ],
    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's denote the monthly incomes of m, n, o, p, and q as M, N, O, P, and Q respectively.\n\nFrom the given information, we can set up the following equations:\n\n1. (M + N) / 2 = 5050\n2. (N + O) / 2 = 6250\n3. (O + P) / 2 = 6800\n4. (P + Q) / 2 = 7500\n5. (M + O + Q) / 3 = 6000\n\nNow, let's solve these equations step by step.\n\nFrom equation 1:\nM + N = 2 * 5050\nM + N = 10100 ... (6)\n\nFrom equation 2:\nN + O = 2 * 6250\nN + O = 12500 ... (7)\n\nFrom equation 3:\nO + P = 2 * 6800\nO + P = 13600 ... (8)\n\nFrom equation 4:\nP + Q = 2 * 7500\nP + Q = 15000 ... (9)\n\nFrom equation 5:\nM + O + Q = 3 * 6000\nM + O + Q = 18000 ... (10)\n\nNow, let's subtract equation 6 from equation 7 to find O:\nN + O - (M + N) = 12500 - 10100\nO - M = 2400 ... (11)\n\nNext, let's subtract equation 8 from equation 9 to find Q:\nP + Q - (O + P) = 15000 - 13600\nQ - O = 1400 ... (12)\n\nNow, let's add equations 11 and 12 to find M:\nO - M + Q - O = 2400 + 1400\nQ - M = 3800 ... (13)\n\nNow, let's add equation 13 to equation 10 to find Q:\nQ - M + M + O + Q = 3800 + 18000\n2Q + O = 21800 ... (14)\n\nWe can now find O by substituting equation 8 into equation 14:\n2Q + (13600 - P) = 21800\n2Q = 21800 - 13600 + P\n2Q = 8200 + P ... (15)\n\nNow, let's subtract equation 9 from equation 15 to find P:\n2Q - (P + Q) = 8200 + P - 15000\nQ - P = -6800 ... (16)\n\nNow, let's add equation 16 to equation 9 to find Q:\nQ - P + P + Q = -6800 + 15000\n2Q = 8200\nQ = 4100 ... (17)\n\nNow that we have Q, we can find P using equation 9:\nP + 4100 = 15000\nP = 15000 - 4100\nP = 10900 ... (18)\n\nNext, we can find O using equation 8:\nO + 10900 = 13600\nO = 13600 - 10900\nO = 2700 ... (19)\n\nNow, we can find N using equation 7:\nN + 2700 = 12500\nN = 12500 - 2700\nN = 9800 ... (20)\n\nFinally, we can find M using equation 6:\nM + 9800 = 10100\nM = 10100 - 9800\nM = 300 ... (21)\n\nSo, the monthly incomes of each individual are:\nM = Rs. 300\nN = Rs. 9800\nO = Rs. 2700\nP = Rs. 10900\nQ = Rs. 4100",
