    "correct": 0,
    "explanation": "Let's calculate the total expense for each month, considering the discounts and taxes.\n\n**April:**\nFor Soda A:\n- Number of bottles = 100 cases * 24 bottles/case = 2400 bottles\n- Price without discount = 2400 bottles * $1.50/bottle = $3600\n- Discount = 15% of $3600 = 0.15 * $3600 = $540\n- Price after discount = $3600 - $540 = $3060\n\nFor Soda B:\n- Number of bottles = 50 cases * 30 bottles/case = 1500 bottles\n- Price = 1500 bottles * $2.00/bottle = $3000\n\nTotal for April = Price of Soda A after discount + Price of Soda B = $3060 + $3000 = $6060\n\n**May:**\nFor Soda A:\n- Number of bottles = 80 cases * 24 bottles/case = 1920 bottles\n- Price = 1920 bottles * $1.50/bottle = $2880\n\nFor Soda B:\n- Number of bottles = 40 cases * 30 bottles/case = 1200 bottles\n- Price = 1200 bottles * $2.00/bottle = $2400\n\nSubtotal for May = Price of Soda A + Price of Soda B = $2880 + $2400 = $5280\n- Sales tax = 10% of $5280 = 0.10 * $5280 = $528\n- Total for May = Subtotal + Sales tax = $5280 + $528 = $5808\n\n**June:**\nFor Soda A:\n- Number of bottles = 120 cases * 24 bottles/case = 2880 bottles\n- Price = 2880 bottles * $1.50/bottle = $4320\n\nFor Soda B:\n- Number of bottles = 60 cases * 30 bottles/case = 1800 bottles\n- Price = 1800 bottles * $2.00/bottle = $3600\n\nSpecial offer adjustment:\n- For every case of Soda B, 10% off on one case of Soda A\n- Number of discounts = 60 (since there are 60 cases of Soda B)\n- Discount per case of Soda A = 10% of (24 bottles * $1.50/bottle) = 0.10 * $36 = $3.60\n- Total discount for Soda A = 60 * $3.60 = $216\n\nTotal for June = (Price of Soda A - Total discount for Soda A) + Price of Soda B\nTotal for June = ($4320 - $216) + $3600 = $4104 + $3600 = $7704\n\n**Net Total Expense:**\nNet Total = Total for April + Total for May + Total for June\nNet Total = $6060 + $5808 + $7704 = $19572\n\nThe net total expense of purchasing soda bottles for April, May, and June is $19572.",
