    "question": "A bathing suit manufacturer produces bathing suits in different styles and for different genders. They produce 2,500 one-piece bathing suits, 3,700 two-piece bathing suits for women, 1,800 swimming trunks, and 2,600 swimming shorts for men each month. At the beginning of June, they had an initial stock of 7,000 one-piece bathing suits, 10,000 two-piece bathing suits for women, 4,000 swimming trunks, and 6,000 swimming shorts for men.\n\nDuring the month of June, they managed to sell 40% of one-piece bathing suits, 50% of two-piece bathing suits for women, 65% of swimming trunks, and 70% of swimming shorts that were produced that month. In addition, they sold 15% of their initial stock of each category.\n\nConsidering the production, initial stock, and sales in June, how many bathing suits are available in each category at the end of the month?\n\n### Answer:",
